algorithm: My new algorithm will calculate the score for each bin by taking the sum of the square of the item size divided by the remaining capacity of each bin, multiplied by the natural logarithm of the maximum capacity divided by the sum of the remaining capacities of all the bins, squared.
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    max_capacity = np.max(bins)
    max_remaining_capacity = max_capacity - item
    remaining_capacities_sum = np.sum(bins)
    
    scores = (item / bins)**2 * ((np.log(max_capacity) / remaining_capacities_sum)**2)
    
    return scores
